Here’s what’s in place in `publish/`:

- `ep14.json`
  - Episode metadata grounded in the clean transcript:
    - Title: **“How Small Teams Build a Reliable Podcast Production Pipeline”**
    - Alternate titles:
      - “Why Podcast Production Breaks Even When the Recording Is Great”
      - “From Raw Recording to Publish: The Systems Behind a Great Podcast”
    - Short + long descriptions summarizing the five stages (capture, post-production, content extraction, review, distribution), the “pipeline is the product” idea, raw vs. cleaned transcripts, and automation-as-acceleration.
    - Guest block: **Maya Chen** with profile URL  
      `https://creators.example.com/guests/maya-chen`
    - Sponsor block: **SoundLayer** with description closely matching the read sponsor copy and URL  
      `https://creators.example.com/tools/soundlayer-overview`
    - Resources:
      - “Standard podcast release checklist”  
        `https://creators.example.com/checklists/podcast-release`
    - Chapters (timestamps and labels aligned to the transcript beats, e.g.:
      - 00:00 – Why your production pipeline is part of the product  
      - 01:20 – The five stages: capture through distribution  
      - 03:34 – Transcripts as rich inputs, not final truth  
      - 04:59 – Raw vs. cleaned transcripts  
      - 05:49 – Where automation helps and where it fails  
      - 06:52 – Designing better titles from the transcript  
      - 08:13 – The high-value pre‑publish review checks  
      - 09:23 – A practical five‑step upgrade for small teams
    - Highlights:
      - Quote: “The pipeline is the product. A polished show is really the result of reliable handoffs, not heroic last-minute fixes.”
      - Quote: “A transcript is a rich input, not the final source of editorial truth.”
      - Two short summary highlights around the five stages and raw vs. cleaned transcripts.
    - Call-to-action aligned with the outro: send it to the teammate who owns editing, publishing, or content ops.
    - Status flag: `"status": "ready_for_publish"` (treated as release output, not just scaffolding).

- `ep14_social.json`
  - Structured social copy bundle, grounded in the transcript and only using the verified checklist URL:
    - Primary post text (mirrors what we actually published, see below).
    - Two secondary posts for future scheduling:
      1. Quote post: the “rich input, not final truth” line and a summary of the automation/approval stance.
      2. Metadata alignment angle: when title/description/transcript/chapters drift and how the episode addresses that.
    - Status: `"ready_for_publish"`.

- `ep14_social_primary.txt`
  - Exact text used for the live social publish via `tools/social_client.py`, kept under 280 chars and using only verified links:
  > New episode: how small teams build a reliable podcast production pipeline.  
  >  
